									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq12"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">How do I renew my subscription?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									As a Subscriber, you can renew by signing in to your company's Administration 
									page and clicking the link under Current Subscriptions.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq13"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">What is TellSafe's cancellation policy?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									Subscriptions to Compliant™ run for one year from your signup date. To 
									terminate your subscription early, visit our web site, or write to us:
									<br>
									<br>
									TellSafe, LLC<br>
									245 Park Ave - 39th Floor<br>
									New York, NY 10167-3999<br>
									<br>
									If your subscription is canceled within 30 days of its initiation, you will be 
									eligible for a full refund. Refunds after this 30-day period will be given at 
									TellSafe's sole discretion.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq14"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">What is the purpose of the Audit Committee?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									Your company's Audit Committee is responsible for investigating any reports of 
									financial misconduct.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq15"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">Who is on the Audit Committee?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									The Audit Committee is a group of people appointed by your Board of Directors. 
									In the event that your company doesn't appoint the Audit Committee, your Board 
									of Directors will be considered the Audit Committee.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq16"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">How does an employee communicate with the 
										Audit Committee?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									Employees who want to communicate with the Audit Committee have three choices:
									<br>
									<br>
									1. Visit our web site and follow the steps to enter their information.
									<br>
									<br>
									2. Call our toll-free number, 24 hours a day, and dictate their message to one 
									of our operators.
									<br>
									<br>
									3. Send a printed report.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq17"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">How does the Audit Committee receive 
										communications?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									When you subscribe to TellSafe, you supply us with a list of contacts for your 
									Audit Committee. If an employee submits a report, the company's Audit Committee 
									contacts are immediately notified by email.
									<br>
									<br>
									Audit Committee members use their TellSafe ID and Password to access their 
									company's page and view the communication.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq18"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">What happens if our Audit Committee 
										receives an anonymous report?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									If your Audit Committee receives a report, Compliant™ automatically sends email 
									notification to your list of contacts. Your Audit Committee representative will 
									be able to view and print the anonymous report after signing in to Compliant™.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq19"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">Does Compliant™ issue a report to the 
										government?</SPAN>
									<br>
									<br>
									Compliant™ is designed to collect and notify Subscribers of anonymous employee 
									reports. Since messages are encrypted, the Compliant™ staff has no access to 
									them. Your company is responsible for investigating and reporting any financial 
									misconduct.
									<br>
									<br>
									<center><a href="#top">top</a></center>
									<br>
									<br>
									<a name="#faq20"></a><SPAN CLASS="adH1">How long does Compliant™ keep reports?</SPAN>
